Xoxo
Goodnight 
T

node.text:
🌀🌀Curl Chronicles⁣ 🌀🌀
⁣
My hair was desperate for a serious refresh and the Camille Rose Honey 🍯 Collection is the sweetest gift to my hair 🎁 
⁣
My curls are loving the new honey collection from @camillerosenaturals ⁣🍯 🐝 
⁣
I used the fresh honey nectar deep treatment to bring back definition and bounce and followed up with the honey leave in, honeycomb curl whip and a little bit of the spiked honey mousse for added moisture. ⁣
⁣
Best of all, I love supporting amazing sister friend entrepreneurs and black owned businesses founded by the one the only 👏🏾👏🏾@janell_stephens!⁣
⁣
You can find these products and more of the #camillerosenaturals product line at @Target stores and online at camillerose.com” ⁣

Check out my stories for a direct link to buy! 
⁣
#Camille⁣rose #honeynectar #skinaunaturale #curlcommunity

node.text:
I found the bestest Ghanaian bead shoppe in town wandering around Osu, it’s tucked behind Woodin and run by a female business owner and entrepreneur 💪🏾 💃🏽 📿⁣
⁣
Beads are a fundamental part of Ghanaian heritage. Not only are they testament to the vibrance of Ghanaian creativity, but they also play a significant role in the country’s history, rituals, culture and were even used as a trading currency 💰⁣
⁣
The original authentic beads are created from layers of powdered glass mixed with dyes and poured into moulds. After heating and cooling, the finished bead is sometimes hand-painted with original designs.⁣
⁣
Ghanaian craftsmen and women smash old or broken bottles into pieces as big as peppercorns. The end product is heated in a wood fire and polished to perfection. ⁣
⁣
There are many other types of beads made in many ways but just sharing this here for you ❤️🇬🇭 ⁣
⁣
#africanbeads #beads #africa #ghanabeads #wasitbeads #beyondthereturn @beyondthereturn

✨i am exactly where i am supposed to be ✨🙏🏾⁣
 
I love this photo.  I am surrounded by things old and new things.  Smiling and looking up into the future.  Surrounded by the art of my ancestors who uplift and support me in all I endeavor.  Who whisper to me when I’m uncertain or worried or have doubts.  They are there are to remind us we are infinite and abundant beings and that my dreams are my reality.  Today, I am blessed and filled with gratitude 🙏🏾 ⁣
⁣

#blessed #grateful

node.text:
🇬🇭 Beyond the Return 🇬🇭 ⁣
⁣
Yesterday I was sashed with an authentic Ghanaian kente sash to honor and welcome those who have returned to Ghana from the Diaspora. ⁣ Thank you Mr. Akwasi Agyeman 
CEO of the Ghana Tourism Authority for the honor @beyondthereturn 
⁣
African Diaspora is the term commonly used to describe the mass dispersion of peoples from Africa during the Transatlantic Slave Trades, from the 1500s to the 1800s. This Diaspora took millions of people from Western and Central Africa to diﬀerent regions throughout the Americas and the Caribbean.⁣
⁣
Ghana’s Beyond the Return initiative was created to welcome and encourage people to return to Ghana, experience the culture, invest in our beautiful country. ⁣
⁣
My Dad was born and raised here in Accra and went abroad to Canada for medical school.  He returned to serve as a military doctor and then came back to Canada and practiced as a OBGYN in Toronto for decades, where he met my mum.  Although I was born in Toronto I grew up visiting Ghana and love to return home to Accra. ⁣
⁣
I have loved sharing my experiences and welcome you ALL to return home and experience Ghana 🇬🇭 ❤️⁣ Akwaaba- you are welcome 🙏🏾 
⁣
⁣
#visitGhana #experienceGhana #yearofthereturn #beyondthereturn #africa #accraghana #ghana #diaspora
